window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>From the alluring book 'A Girl Named Harper' comes the highly anticipated second installment, A Girl Named Joy. Dive back into the romantic saga that began with Harper’s journey and continues with Joy’s story.<br> <br> Joy's smile masks a lifetime of hidden pain. Rejected by her parents during childhood, she's grown up feeling that love is fleeting and trust is fragile. Now a young adult, she struggles to let anyone close, fearing the pain of abandonment all over again.<br> <br> Enter Xavier, a whirlwind of charm and good looks, drawing Joy in despite her lingering resentment towards his cousin Harper, which threatens to drive a wedge between them. As an unforeseen tragedy shakes her world and those around her, Joy is faced with the challenge of discovering the meaning of true family. Can Harper and Joy reconcile their differences and forge a friendship, or will their tumultuous relationship force Xavier into a difficult choice?<br> <br> 'A Girl Named Joy' is a touching narrative of love, loss, and redemption that tests the strength of friendship and the power of forgiveness. Accompany Joy on her journey of self-discovery as she realizes that sometimes, it's in our darkest moments that we find the courage to embrace the light.</p>"; 
